content: Overall, a very enjoyable game. My only complaint is that some puzzles have very poor instruction on how the puzzles function. I've found that in all the 5 by games so far. At least one can choose to skip them, so you don't get hopelessly stuck in the progress of the game. It's just of kind of frustrating to skip a puzzle just because you have no idea what the mechanics of it are.
I love it..they keep getting better and better..

I like the storyline. The graphics are high quality. but especially the puzzles are very different than what I have seen before and the other games that I have played. That by itself is the best part of this game and the previous one number one
Great entertainment
Great fun, I bought the full game after playing the free one.

PROs: Excellent graphics, fun puzzles, and this might be my favorite story from 5-BN so far. Also, almost all of the puzzles and collection objects were large & clear enough to see and manipulate on my phone. CONs: I didn't care for the two timed HOPs, I wish after finishing a puzzle I could look at it for more than a fraction of a second before it disappears. OVERALL: It's well worth the price (especially if you liked Lost Lands) and hopefully 5-BN will release #4 on Google Play soon!

Please, try to open the Options menu (from the Main menu) and check the Voice settings there - probably, you need to add more volume to the Voice settings. If this solution doesn't help, please write to support@five-bn.com, describe the problem in detail, and we’ll do our best to assist you.

Best regards,

Darkness and Flame #3 has disappeared! Guess Google Play is driving me to the 'other' online merchant. 8-( Wonderful series along w Lost Lands for replay value and exceptional game play.
replyContent: Hi Mary! Thank you for appreciation of our games! Darkness and Flame 3 hasn't been released on Google Play yet. Unfortunately, we have faced some technical difficulties with releasing our games on Google Play, and our developers are working hard to overcome them. Darkness and Flame 3 will be released on Google Play, but a bit later that we expected

content:
This part two was better than Darkness and Flame part one. Still I was 
little bit disappointed that there isn't much about the flame, only couple 
videoclips. It would be much better if player could use the flame, like 
some games there's a little helper and player can use that helper to solve 
tasks. In this two part game of Darkness and Flame the idea is good but how 
it's done leaves you feeling empty. Anyway everything works, graphics are 
beautiful and there's lot of playing and doing.
replyContent: Hi Helina! Thank you for your feedback! We'll take into consideration your advice about "little helper". Maybe we'll use this idea in some of our upcoming games. Thank you for sharing your opinion with us and for playing our games!

I enjoyed this follow up story.  It had the usual map, collections, scrolls and the graphics were great. The plot was okay and you learnt a bit more of the background sorry. It had some good tasks and games, again for me some were really too easy and altho you can  change the difficulty of the game I wish you could choose to make the mini games harder. I also wish you did a puzzle/s in say the first half an hour to build up a multi tool with a knife, matches, lock pick etc that you then keep throughout the game (and could add too depending what world you're in). I have enjoyed all of this developers games including this one altho this was quite a bit shorter.  Overall it was a good way to kill a few hours and even though I got this on offer I think I would've paid full price.

Another excellent games from five-bn!

Absolutely superb game! Extremely well made, smooth, easy to navigate, stunning artwork, imaginative story & I loved the imaginative hidden object scenes; some of which were reversed so that items had to be placed correctly instead of found. Five Bn always manage to produce games that have the highest quality graphics that I have ever seen & have an extra depth that seems unique to their games. I really liked that it was possible to see on the map where there were morphing objects & collectibles to be found as this enabled me to ensure I found them all! The puzzles were enjoyable & just the right level of difficulty too. I enjoyed every single minute of this game & so didn't want it to end. A really well thought out game. Absolute perfection!
